RADIO: The time is 8:12 AM. Before we begin our morning bulletin, a local reminder from the Ministry of Civil Defense: [next=1]

Citizens registered with Class-3 Strength or higher are requested at the eastern rail yard this afternoon to assist with cargo offloading. Additionally, unregistered levitation during twilight hours remains strictly prohibited. [next=2]

RADIO: Moving to regional defense... The general air-raid alert for the Kiyoshima district has been officially lifted. [next=1.5]

Radar has detected a lone, high-altitude aircraft approaching from the east. Command assesses it as a routine weather or reconnaissance flight. No kinetic interception or barrier deployment is required at this time. [next=2]

RADIO: Citizens may return to their standard morning duties. Remain vigilant, but there is no immediate danger. [next=1]
